[FILE:279:descriptions/desc.single]
The Cantarell typeface family is a contemporary Humanist sans serif, and 
is used by the GNOME project for its user interface.

Cantarell only distributes a variable font since version 0.303 instead of 
the previously available seperate fonts for bold, light, regular and so on.


